caption:
It has been a most incredible 16 months. This is the B-Society 23-24 executive team signing off for the last time. 

To the general engineering student body, it was a privilege and an honor to serve the B-Society undergraduate engineering student body throughout these last 16 months. Please continue to engage with the society as it is taken to new heights.

To the previous executive teams that have come before us, thank you for being the giants whose shoulders we stood on. Thank you for the work you put into the society, and the strong foundations that we were able to build upon. 

And finally to the incoming executive team, we wish you nothing but the best. It has been a pleasure to work with all of you in your previous capacities, and we are sure that your passion, enthusiasm, and hard work will carry you far in your new positions.

- Dylan, Jake, Grace, Michael, and Thomas

caption:
Here are our award winners for S24!

Engineering Society Leadership Excellence Award
Awarded to someone who displays leadership within the Faculty, University and/or community at-large. Congrats to Amir!

Igor Ivkovic Teaching Excellence Award
Awarded to a member of the teaching team within the University of Waterloo Engineering Faculty rewarding teaching excellence. The Award, previously called the ‚ÄúTeaching Excellence Award‚Äù, was renamed after Igor Ivkovic, a Systems Design Engineering Professor, who exemplified the spirit of the Award. He dedicated his life to his students, colleagues, and the University of Waterloo community. He advanced teaching in Engineering through his care and enthusiasm. The Award was renamed to honour his legacy and to promote his dedication to our community. The students, faculty and Waterloo community will always remember how much Professor Igor cared. Congratulations to Reem Roufail!

Friend of Natalie Award
Awarded to a Faculty and Staff Member who have gone out of their way to support the mental health of students. Congrats to Pendar Mahmoudi!

Paul Harlick Award
Awarded to the most engaged and enthusiastic class reps! Congrats Jordan and Garvit EE '28. 

President's Awards
Awarded by each of B-Soc Exec to commissioners/directors who have given their all to improve our society! Congrats to Muhammad, Sumnit, Lino, Celia, and Kate

The Engineering Society is currently looking to form its team of Commissioners for the Fall 2024 Academic term!

We employ Commissioners to assist the executive with the Society's day-to-day operations and explore potential avenues for growth in the Society. Commissioners work closely with Directors and Executives to ensure that all the Society's services and events run successfully. These positions will be for seven months, from June 2024 to December 2024.

We require commissioners to be undergraduate Waterloo Engineering Students. Both on and off term students are encouraged to apply, but preference will be given those on-term in the fall students.

Application can be found here: https://bit.ly/F24CommApplications. Link in bio!

Deadline to Apply: Sunday, May 26th at 11:59pm

On one hand, UX design is‚Ä¶
üëâ focused on creating beautiful interfaces and building seamless interaction, and ensure the whole user experience is enjoyable
‚≠êÔ∏è is a more specialized role as they have a more specific, design-oriented focus in their responsibilities
üß∞ experience can be involved with interaction design, visual design, UX research, and other similar roles

On the other hand, product design‚Ä¶
üîé is involved with the entire product creation process, with a more business-oriented focus as they are responsible for discovering and defining a problem and creating a design solution
‚ú® sometimes associated with physical design, also known as industrial design
üí≠ experience can be involved in project and/or product management, UX design, and more!

caption:
Wesley Chun, one of the speakers at Hack with AI, talked about ‚ÄúReflections on a career in Software Engineering‚Äù today.

üìç SPEAKER BIO
WESLEY CHUN, MSCS, is a Google Developer Expert (GDE) in Google Cloud (GCP) & Google Workspace (GWS), author of Prentice Hall‚Äôs bestselling ‚ÄúCore Python‚Äù (corepython.com) series, co-author of ‚ÄúPython Web Development with Django‚Äù (withdjango.com), and has written for Linux Journal & CNET. He runs CyberWeb (cyberwebconsulting.com) specializing in Google developer tools/platforms, Python & App Engine migrations (appenginemigrations.com), and technical training. Wesley was one of the original Yahoo!Mail engineers and spent a dozen plus years on various Google product teams, covering their APIs on-stage, producing sample apps, tutorials, and serverless migration & GWS developers video series. He holds degrees in Computer Science, Mathematics, and Music from the University of California, is a Fellow of the Python Software Foundation, and loves to meet developers worldwide at conferences, user group events, and universities. Follow he/him @wescpy & dev.to/wescpy.

caption:
WAT.ai is recruiting for Director positions! 

WAT.ai is both the Undergraduate Body of the Waterloo A.I. Institute and a member of the Sedra Student Design Centre. Our goal is to establish an environment to grow the future of AI talent at Waterloo. We provide opportunities to engage in impactful AI projects in concentrated research groups, providing educational resources and innovative challenges. If you want to be a part of the future of AI, there is no better time than now. Join us! 

We are looking to recruit several non-technical leadership roles, including Education Director, Finance Director, Marketing Director, Partnerships Director, and Website Director. Interviews will be done throughout July, the deadline to apply is July 31st!
